{{docs-hero}}

<div class="docs-container docs-md">
  <section class="docs-max-w-md docs-mx-auto docs-pb-8">
    <h2 class="docs-flex docs-items-center docs-mt-8 docs-h2">
      Motivation
    </h2>

    <aside>Looking to get started? {{docs-link "Click here" "docs"}}.</aside>

    <p>
      The `ember-intl` addon and all of it's provided functionality is wonderful. What is
      challenging with the `Intl` specification, is the ability to optimally and
      consistently format dates and time in long, medium, short, ... formats. Something akin
      to the locale-formatting that `momentjs` has provided us for years.
    </p>

    <p>
      As a result of this challenge, we created this simple set of Ember helpers to
      format dates consistently and with performance at top of mind. Here are a few
      examples of the helpers you get with this addon:
    </p>

    <ul class="fa-ul">
      <li>
        <span class="fa-li">{{fa-icon "code"}}</span>
        <code>\{{date-format-l now}}</code>
        {{fa-icon "long-arrow-alt-right" fixedWidth=true}}
        {{date-format-l now}}
      </li>
      <li>
        <span class="fa-li">{{fa-icon "code"}}</span>
        <code>\{{date-format-llllz now}}</code>
        {{fa-icon "long-arrow-alt-right" fixedWidth=true}}
        {{date-format-llllz now}}
      </li>
      <li>
        <span class="fa-li">{{fa-icon "code"}}</span>
        <code>\{{date-short-lllz now}}</code>
        {{fa-icon "long-arrow-alt-right" fixedWidth=true}}
        {{date-short-lllz now}}
      </li>
    </ul>

    <h2 class="docs-flex docs-items-center docs-mt-8 docs-h2">
      Discover An Issue?
